(1) file system security

data->folder/directory,file

operation-> read,write,execute


commands->chmod(change mode),

example-> chmod -x /bin/test(remove execute permission from test file)

(chomd permission filename)

ls -l(show the permission for your file)
+  -> add permission
-  -> remove permission
=  ->override permission



USERS IN OS -> owner/user(u),group(g),other(o)
chmod g+x test(execute permission for group)

chmod o=rwx test (all permission for other)

chmod u-r test (remove read permission from user)


"file creator called owner"


chown(change owner)

syntax  -> chown user file

newgrp   ->creat new group


#add new user

command -> adduser name

#add group
command -> groupadd name

~
